                <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
                <path d="M12 16v-4"></path>
                <path d="M12 8h.01"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="callout-content">
              <strong>Key Difference from Other GTA Cities:</strong> Vaughan uses 29 days as the STR threshold, while Toronto uses 28 days and Mississauga uses 30 days. This affects what counts as a short-term vs. mid-term rental.
            </div>
          </div>

          <h2 id="no-night-limit">No Annual Night Limit</h2>
          <p>One significant advantage of Vaughan's STR regulations compared to Toronto and Mississauga:</p>

          <div class="highlight-box">
            <h4>Vaughan Has No Annual Night Limit</h4>
            <p>Unlike Toronto and Mississauga (both 180 days/year), Vaughan does not impose a cap on how many nights you can rent your principal residence as a short-term rental.</p>
          </div>

          <p>This means if you have a licensed STR at your principal residence in Vaughan, you can technically operate it year-round without hitting a regulatory ceiling. However, you must still:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Maintain a valid license</li>
            <li>Keep it as your principal residence</li>
            <li>Comply with all other bylaw requirements</li>
            <li>Collect and remit the 4% MAT</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 id="principal-residence">The Principal Residence Rule</h2>
          <p>This is the most important rule for prospective hosts to understand. Vaughan only allows STRs at your principal residence:</p>

          <blockquote class="bylaw-quote">
            "Principal Residence means a dwelling unit owned or rented by an Individual Person, either alone or jointly with others, where the Individual Person is ordinarily resident."
            <cite>Vaughan By-Law 158-2019, Section 3.0(4)(aa)</cite>
          </blockquote>

          <p>The property must be:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>The <strong>principal residence</strong> of at least one of the applicants</li>
            <li>Located in an area that <strong>permits residential uses</strong></li>
            <li>In compliance with the <strong>Ontario Building Code and Fire Code</strong></li>
          </ul>

          <div class="warning-box">
            <h4>What This Means for Property Investors</h4>
            <p>If you own an investment property, vacation home, or second property in Vaughan, you <strong>cannot</strong> operate it as a short-term rental. The principal residence rule means you can only STR the home where you actually live.</p>
            <p>Looking to rent an investment property? Consider <a href="/services/mid-term-rental-management">mid-term rentals</a> (30+ days) which are exempt from these restrictions.</p>
          </div>

          <h2 id="mid-term-strategy">Mid-Term Rentals: The Alternative Strategy</h2>
          <p>Since Vaughan's STR rules only apply to rentals of 29 days or less, <strong>mid-term rentals are completely exempt</strong> from these regulations.</p>

          <h3>What Qualifies as Mid-Term?</h3>
          <p>Any rental of 30 consecutive days or more in Vaughan:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Does <strong>not</strong> require an STR license</li>
            <li>Does <strong>not</strong> require principal residence status</li>
            <li>Can be operated on investment properties</li>
            <li>Is not subject to the MAT</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="strategy-box">
            <h4>Why Mid-Term Works Well in Vaughan</h4>
            <p>Vaughan has strong mid-term rental demand due to:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Corporate relocations:</strong> Major employers like CN, FedEx, and numerous corporate headquarters</li>
              <li><strong>Canada's Wonderland:</strong> Seasonal workers during peak season</li>
              <li><strong>Healthcare workers:</strong> Proximity to Mackenzie Health hospital</li>
              <li><strong>Construction projects:</strong> Ongoing development throughout York Region</li>
              <li><strong>New immigrants:</strong> Vaughan has a large newcomer population</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h2 id="license-requirements">License Requirements</h2>
          <p>Before operating any STR in Vaughan, you must obtain a license from the city.</p>

          <h3>Who Can Get a License?</h3>
          <p>Licenses are only available to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Individual persons</strong> (not corporations, partnerships, or other business entities)</li>
            <li>Persons with <strong>permanent residency in Canada</strong></li>
            <li>Persons <strong>18 years of age or older</strong></li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Application Requirements</h3>
          <p>To apply for an STR Owner license in Vaughan, you must provide:</p>
          <ol>
            <li><strong>Completed application form</strong> signed by all applicants</li>
            <li><strong>Proof of ownership or tenancy</strong></li>
            <li><strong>License fee</strong> (non-refundable)</li>
            <li><strong>Proof of Canadian permanent residency</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Government-issued photo ID</strong> for all applicants</li>
            <li><strong>Vulnerable Sector Check</strong> from an Ontario Police Service (within 90 days)</li>
            <li><strong>Proof of principal residence</strong></li>
            <li><strong>List of all STR operators</strong> with contact information</li>
            <li><strong>MAT registration</strong> (must register before applying for license)</li>
          </ol>

          <div class="callout">
            <div class="callout-icon">
              <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
                <path d="M12 16v-4"></path>
                <path d="M12 8h.01"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="callout-content">
              <strong>For Tenants:</strong> If you rent your home, you need an original, notarized letter from your landlord giving explicit permission to operate an STR. The letter must be certified by a notary public or commissioner of oaths.
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>License Validity and Renewal</h3>
          <p>STR licenses in Vaughan:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Must be renewed <strong>annually</strong> by the anniversary date</li>
            <li>Can be renewed no earlier than 2 months before the anniversary</li>
            <li>If lapsed up to 30 days: 15% late fee applies</li>
            <li>If lapsed 30-90 days: 30% late fee applies</li>
            <li>If lapsed more than 90 days: license is <strong>cancelled</strong> and you cannot reapply for 2 years</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 id="background-check">Background Check Requirements</h2>
          <p>Vaughan requires a comprehensive background check for all STR license applicants:</p>

          <blockquote class="bylaw-quote">
            "A complete Vulnerable Sector Check for every Applicant, issued by an Ontario Police Service, not more than 90 days old, from the date of application."
            <cite>Vaughan By-Law 158-2019, Section 5.0(13)(g)</cite>
          </blockquote>

          <h3>Automatic Disqualifications</h3>
          <p>You cannot obtain a license if, within the previous 5 years, you have been convicted of:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Homicide or manslaughter</li>
            <li>Sexual offences</li>
            <li>Assault offences</li>
            <li>Confinement offences</li>
            <li>Robbery or extortion</li>
            <li>Break and enter</li>
            <li>Fraud or forgery</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 id="property-types">What Properties Qualify?</h2>
          <p>STRs can only be operated in a dwelling unit that is your principal residence.</p>

          <h3>Allowed</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Single-family homes</li>
            <li>Townhouses</li>
            <li>Condo units (if condo corporation permits)</li>
            <li>Apartments (with landlord authorization)</li>
            <li>Part of your dwelling unit (room rentals)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Additional Requirements for Condos/Multi-Unit Buildings</h3>
          <blockquote class="bylaw-quote">
            "If the proposed Short-Term Rental is to be located in a Multiple Unit Dwelling, Applicants shall provide, at the time of application, a letter from the owner of such Multiple Unit Dwelling declaring that the Operation of Short-Term Rentals is permitted."
            <cite>Vaughan By-Law 158-2019, Section 5.0(9)</cite>
          </blockquote>

          <p>This means you need written permission from your condo corporation or building owner before the city will even consider your application.</p>

          <h2 id="compliance">Compliance Requirements</h2>
          <p>Once licensed, you must follow these ongoing requirements:</p>

          <h3>Display Your License</h3>
          <blockquote class="bylaw-quote">
            "Every Short-Term Rental Owner shall post the licence supplied by the City at the time of issuance or renewal in a conspicuous place visible from the outside of the Dwelling Unit, on, or as near as possible to, the main entrance to the Short-Term Rental."
            <cite>Vaughan By-Law 158-2019, Section 11.0(8)</cite>
          </blockquote>

          <h3>No Overlapping Bookings</h3>
          <blockquote class="bylaw-quote">
            "No Short-Term Rental Owner shall offer or accept multiple reservations where the proposed accommodation Rental Periods of said reservations overlap."
            <cite>Vaughan By-Law 158-2019, Section 11.0(2)</cite>
          </blockquote>

          <h3>Building Code Compliance</h3>
          <p>Your property must comply with both the Ontario Building Code and Fire Code. The city may require an inspection before issuing or renewing your license.</p>

          <h3>Only Use Licensed Brokerages</h3>
          <p>You can only list your STR through platforms that hold a valid City of Vaughan brokerage license. Major platforms like Airbnb typically have this, but verify before listing elsewhere.</p>

          <h3>Record Keeping</h3>
          <p>Brokerages (and by extension, hosts working with them) must maintain records for <strong>3 years</strong> including:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Number of nights rented</li>
            <li>Nightly and total prices charged</li>
            <li>Whether it was entire-unit or partial-unit rental</li>
            <li>MAT collected on each transaction</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 id="why-worth-it">Why STR Is Worth It in Vaughan</h2>
          <p>Despite the regulations, operating a licensed STR in Vaughan offers significant advantages:</p>

          <h3>1. No Night Limit</h3>
          <p>Unlike Toronto and Mississauga's 180-day caps, Vaughan allows year-round STR operation at your principal residence. This maximizes your earning potential.</p>

          <h3>2. Strong Location Demand</h3>
          <p>Vaughan attracts visitors due to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Canada's Wonderland:</strong> Millions of visitors annually need nearby accommodation</li>
            <li><strong>Vaughan Mills:</strong> Major shopping destination</li>
            <li><strong>Corporate headquarters:</strong> Business travelers visiting offices</li>
            <li><strong>TTC Subway access:</strong> Line 1 extension makes Vaughan accessible to Toronto</li>
            <li><strong>Events and weddings:</strong> Numerous event venues in the area</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>3. Premium Pricing</h3>
          <p>Vaughan's suburban setting with larger homes commands premium rates compared to downtown Toronto condos, especially for families and groups.</p>

          <h3>4. Professional Support Available</h3>
          <p>Managing compliance, guest communication, and turnover can be time-consuming. Professional property managers like <a href="/">Nurture</a> handle everything including license compliance, guest screening, cleaning coordination, and revenue optimization so you can earn passive income without the day-to-day stress.</p>

          <h2 id="official-resources">Official Resources</h2>
          <p>For the most current and authoritative information, consult these official City of Vaughan sources:</p>

          <div class="resources-box">
            <h4>Official Links</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="https://www.vaughan.ca/residential/short-term-rentals" target="_blank" rel="noopener">City of Vaughan STR Information</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.vaughan.ca/residential/short-term-rentals/apply-short-term-rental-licence" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Apply for an STR License</a></li>
